Created attachment 152020
Extend pkg-message with devd(8) config guide

While not really familar with devd, today I inspected why this "attach" rule wouldn't apply:
attach 10 {
        match "device-name" "nsa[0-9]+";
        action "camcontrol periphlist $device-name | sed -n 's/\(^pass[[:digit:]]\{1,3\}\):[[:blank:]].*/\1/p' | xargs -I PASS chown bacula /dev/PASS";
};

Found out that /usr/local/etc/devd/ is already scanned by devd(8),
so please find attached a patch which guides the user making use of devd(8) to grant bacula sa(4) access.
